03/01/2011
BRUSSELS, Belgium -- Hungarian Prime Minister Viktor Orban, whose country took over the six-month EU presidency on Saturday (January 1st,) says in an interview with the Council of the EU website that speeding up and closing accession talks with Croatia is of strategic importance. 
He added that Hungary will work to draft a joint European strategy for the Roma and provide a European perspective to Western Balkan countries. 
"We will also use every effort to support the accession of Romania and Bulgaria to the Schengen zone," Orban promised. 
(Council of the EU website, Hina, tportal.hr - 01/01/11)
